originalText.text: Had a very mediocre service for $110 gel extension (not gel x, and not including tip). First was surprised that everything cost extra- gel polish in place of regular polish and using harder tips, but maybe that's standard now? At most places I've been it's all included. The sample colors are not even close to what they look like on the nail and the shade was extremely off and translucent (the most frustrating part- I chose a dark red and it was candy red and see through). The shaping was also really strange and made my nails look fake and chubby. During the process itself, I felt like the woman did an ok job, but wasn't being too careful and somehow took 2.5 hours. My nail also broke after a week while not doing anything strenuous that would put my nail in danger- it was likely because it was lifting on the sides already... I ended up having to repaint my nails myself to make it the right shade and then I shaped them myself to make them look more natural. I was expecting it to be less cost for just a solid color extension, or at least because of the cost, to last longer and be better quality.
